HEADWORD: Mucocele
<hw>Mu"co*cele</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Mucus</ets> +
Gr. <grk>kh`lh</grk> tumor.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An enlargement
or protrusion of the mucous membrane of the lachrymal passages, or
dropsy of the lachrymal sac, dependent upon catarrhal inflammation of
the latter.</def> <rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mucoid</ent>⟦br⟧
